# Bench the Curator

## Step

From the neat-memory grilling (Joel, 2026-07-16): "i'd like the
smartest agent we have to decide … the question would be what the skill
is for that agent IMO … maybe we benchmark this too so I can see and
feel what I like."

Resolved when Joel has looked at a prototype page (wiki, like the
loop-language variants page) showing, for the SAME candidate pool
(a real recent window of observations + rollups + retros), what each
judge config would have done — config = model × taste-skill variant:

- Fable via `claude -p` (API spend authorized for this use case)
- `gpt-5.6-sol:xhigh` via pi
- a cheap baseline (terra:low or DeepSeek-local) for contrast

Per config, per day of the window: send or hold, which memory, which
flavor, and the actual DM line it would have written — the feel is in
the line, not the score. Joel picks; the winning config ships as the
LaunchAgent default and the losing receipts stay on the page.

Blocked on the build step only for the judge seam + candidate harness
it produces; the taste-skill variants (2–3, deliberately different
personalities of "neat") are authored here.

## Result — 2026-07-16 (steering, with Joel live)

Closed by Joel's picks, made iteratively against six page versions
(v1–v6 at /prototypes/neat-memory-curator/): **sol:xhigh with the
27-line simple prompt** (`skills/neat-memory-simple-prompt.md`) — the
scaffolded bench prompts, the inlined taste skill, and the 16k voice
skill all lost to it on real per-day runs with zero meta framing.
Along the way Joel reshaped the product: DMs are a couple formatted
paragraphs with emoji, action-biased ("a smol prompt to me"), no
frequency cap — quality + non-repetition are the only gates, and the
curator names its own `nextBeat` (2h–48h clamp) scheduled through the
pane-scheduling inngest machinery; the LaunchAgent demoted to a daily
dead-man. Production adopted it all (joelclaw-observer through
`e6cde337`, release promoted). Live receipts: real send envelope ok
(the curator's first pick under the final config was the memory layer
reporting its own extraction blind spot), beat `a2dffc7b` self-scheduled
at the curator's requested 6h. One validator bug caught live: the
simple prompt's send shape has no `why` — now derived from the dm.

## Result — 2026-07-16 curator bench worker

Status: open / HITL. Joel still needs to pick the winning taste + judge config.
No commit, no push, no deploy, no DMs. Bench was dry-run only; `--apply` was never used and `~/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json` was not written.

Changed surfaces:

- `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer/skills/neat-memory-taste-warm.md` — warmer/nostalgia/weird-scene variant.
- `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer/skills/neat-memory-taste-strict.md` — stricter signal-only variant.
- `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer/.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory-bench.ts` — config-driven dry bench over the same 14-day privacy-gated pool; reuses the shipped candidate/state/judgment/message primitives.
- `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-wiki/static/prototypes/neat-memory-curator/index.html` — static prototype page.
- `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-wiki/static/prototypes/neat-memory-curator/__data.json` — copied bench data for the page.

Bench receipt:

- JSON: `/tmp/neat-memory-bench.json`
- Window: 14 days, observations + retros; dream rollups included as observation pages.
- Privacy gate: production `selectNeatMemoryCandidates`; `privacy: sensitive` and unparseable/missing-frontmatter pages fail closed before judges.
- Counts: 451 source files scanned; 218 eligible candidates; 217 unsent; 32 candidates shown to judges after per-day cap; 4 days; 5 total judge calls.
- Judge matrix:
  - `fable-v1`: 1 call, 1 send / 3 hold.
  - `fable-warm`: 1 call, 1 send / 3 hold.
  - `fable-strict`: 1 call, 1 send / 3 hold.
  - `sol-xhigh-v1`: 1 call, 3 send / 1 hold.
  - `terra-low-v1`: 1 call, 2 send / 2 hold.

Verification:

- `bun .pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory-bench.ts` — wrote `/tmp/neat-memory-bench.json`, all 5 judge configs returned parseable verdict JSON.
- `bun test` in `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer` — 82 pass, 0 fail.

Steering next step: deploy/publish the static prototype page from `joelclaw-wiki` and hand Joel the URL for the pick.
